content.title: Documentation and API
content.body:
We want to make sure that our documentation is clear and easy to use. We also want to make sure that our API is well documented and easy to use.

**Question for community**

- What do you think about our current documentation?
- What do you think about our current API?
- What would you like to see in our documentation and API?

content.title: Ticketing System
content.body:
We want to build a ticketing system that allows users to generate tickets/bug reports, assign tickets to your team, and message users when a ticket is created / responded to / resolved.

**The basics would be:**

- A way of users generating tickets/bug reports
- Assigning tickets to your team
- Messaging users when a ticket is created / responded to / resolved

**We are unclear on (feedback hugely appreciated):**

- If early stage companies would need it to work with discord/slack or if that's unusual
- If you are excited about this because you would happily replace an existing product - which one? Or if you'd just use us as you're not using anything else at the moment

**Beyond this:**

- Some way of prioritizing tickets based on user data
- Integrating session replay and errors into the ticket automatically

content.title: Roadmap page
content.body:
We want to build a roadmap page that allows users to see what we are working on, what is coming next, and what is planned for the future.

**The basics would be:**

- A way of users seeing what we are working on
- A way of users seeing what is coming next
- A way of users seeing what is planned for the future

**We are unclear on (feedback hugely appreciated):**

- If early stage companies would need it to work with discord/slack or if that's unusual
- If you are excited about this because you would happily replace an existing product - which one? Or if you'd just use us as you're not using anything else at the moment
